quotes.text: Strength doesn't come from what you can do; it comes from overcoming the things you once thought you couldn't.
Success is walking from failure to failure with no loss of enthusiasm.
The only bad workout is the one that didn't happen.
Your body can stand almost anything; it's your mind you have to convince.
The harder the battle the sweeter the victory.
Don't count the days; make the days count.
Sweat is just fat crying.
The only person you should try to be better than is the person you were yesterday.
It's not about having time; it's about making time.
Believe in yourself and you will be unstoppable.
Strength grows in the moments when you think you can't go on but keep going anyway.
Success is a journey not a destination.
The pain you feel today will be the strength you feel tomorrow.
Excuses don't burn calories.
Fitness is not about being better than someone else; it's about being better than you used to be.
The body achieves what the mind believes.
The difference between a goal and a dream is a deadline.
Make your vision so clear that your fears become irrelevant.
Winners never quit and quitters never win.
Every workout is a step closer to your goals.
You are only limited by your imagination
Champions aren't built on the days they feel motivated but the days they feel like quitting
No carelessness in my action No confusion in my words No imprecision in my thoughts.
